# Cursor Rules — OpenClaw Knowledge Base

## Project Overview
This is a semantic knowledge base service built as an OpenClaw agent skill.
FastAPI backend + Pinecone vector store + OpenAI embeddings/RAG + vanilla HTML frontend.

## Stack
- Python 3.12, FastAPI, Uvicorn
- Pinecone (serverless, cosine similarity, 1536-dim)
- OpenAI: text-embedding-3-small (embeddings), gpt-4o-mini (RAG)
- tiktoken for token-aware chunking
- pypdf + BeautifulSoup4 for document parsing
- Frontend: plain HTML/CSS/JS in frontend/index.html (no framework)

## Code Style
- Python: use async/await throughout, type hints on all functions
- FastAPI: keep routers thin, business logic lives in services/
- Pydantic v2 for all models (use model_config, not class Config)
- Use httpx.AsyncClient for all HTTP calls, never requests
- Never use print() — use Python logging
- Handle all external API errors with try/except and HTTPException

## Architecture Rules
- server/routers/ — only request parsing + response shaping
- server/services/ — all business logic (embeddings, vectorstore, ingestion, rag)
- server/models/schemas.py — all Pydantic models in one file
- Each Pinecone vector ID format: {doc_id}#chunk#{index}
- Metadata stored on each vector: doc_id, title, chunk, chunk_index, tags, created_at, namespace

## Environment
- All config comes from environment variables (python-dotenv in dev)
- Never hardcode API keys or URLs
- See .env.example for all available variables

## Frontend
- frontend/index.html is a single self-contained file
- Uses CSS variables for theming (all defined in :root)
- Two pages: home (#page-home) and kbhub (#page-kbhub)
- showPage('home') / showPage('kbhub') switches between them
- Color palette: --bg:#0c0b09, --accent:#ff5c00, --gold:#f0c040
- Fonts: Syne (headings), DM Mono (code/mono), DM Sans (body)
- No build step, no npm — keep it that way unless there's a strong reason

## Naming Conventions
- Python files: snake_case
- Python classes: PascalCase
- API routes: /kebab-case
- CSS classes: kebab-case
- JS functions: camelCase

## What Already Exists (don't recreate)
- All 5 API endpoints (ingest, search, ask, documents, health)
- Pinecone init + upsert + query + delete + list
- OpenAI embeddings + chunking
- Text/Markdown/PDF/URL ingestion
- RAG context building + answer generation
- Full homepage + KBHub frontend UI
